				            	<li><p>Eggs are laid in masses, usually on leaf tips and covered with hairs. Eggs hatch in about 5-10 days.</p></li>	              	
								              	
				            	<li><p>Immediately after hatching, first instar larvae disperse with the help of silken threads. 
				            	Initially they feed by scraping on the green matter and later bore into the stem above the water level. 
